list.name: Changes
list.comment: Section 20.331(JavaFX; Reading Files with NIO): introduction to passing index to buffer.getInt() etc as alternative instead of using buffer.flip(); demonstrated how to read data from a channel via reading data into buffers; using buffer.array() and .hasArray() as checks for possible ways to retrieve data from a buffer

task.summary: Section 20.329(JavaFX; Reading and Writing with Java): finishing off the video

Section 20.330(JavaFX; Writing Binary Files with Java NIO): introduction to ByteBuffer, turn string into bytes (byte[], then as buffer ByteBuffer.wrap()), set buffer capacity with ByteBuffer.allocate(), and the requirements of .flip() when switching from read/write viceversa
